post_text: As this year’s Teacher Appreciation Week comes to a close, please know our love and admiration for you all never ends! Now, more than ever before, do we have an even better understanding of the mountains you move on a daily basis to have each child have an “aha!” moment. There is no better feeling in the world than to know your child can do something today that they couldn’t yesterday. Without all of you, those moments would be much fewer and far between. Thank you, each and every one of you, for everything that you mean to our families! We love you Fair Haven teachers!!! #fhleads

post_text:
Dear Fair Haven Families,

I hope you are all enjoying a lovely summer and are all safe during the storm this evening.

I am writing to provide an update to an alarm that caused the FHFD to respond to Knollwood School this evening.

There was no fire. The Fire Department has cleared the building for use.

A partial power outage caused us to lose a phase that in turn caused a water heater pump motor to overheat and burn out.

All is well at Knollwood and assuming power is restored, all summer programs will be in session as normal tomorrow. We do anticipate power to return at some point this evening.

Please extend a big thank you to our firefighters when you see them this year at the fair as they do an incredible job in responding to our community and emergency needs.

You will only be notified if school is closed tomorrow as a result of the power outage. If you do not hear any follow up, Summer Learning Academy and ESY are on as scheduled.

Have a wonderful evening!

post_text: All presentations will feature the same information. We are offering multiple dates so that folks have options to attend in case they have conflicts. Our daytime presentation at Sickles School on May 22nd will be a little more restricted as school is in session and we need to be mindful of our students’ safety; so please aim to come to one of our evening presentations if at all possible. More information on our school bond referendum will be available in the coming days via a tab on our website as well as via posts on our Instagram and Facebook pages. Thank you Fair Haven and we look forward to sharing exactly why we feel these projects are so critical, not only to the future of our community, but for the here and now as well. #FHLeads
